30/01/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- In a letter sent Wednesday (29 January) to US President George W Bush, Prime Minister Fatos Nano said his government's resolve to support the United States in fighting terrorism is "maximal and unconditional". 
He also confirmed his country's support for UN Resolution 1441 asking Iraq to disarm and expressed the "deep concern of [his] government over the violations of human rights by the dictatorial regime of Saddam Hussein". 
(ATA - 29/01/03)
